Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] Taba, 20 Jan (MENA)--The Civilian Affairs and 
Security Committees, which are subcommittees of the Gaza-Jericho 
Committee, resumed meetings this morning in Taba. 
  The Palestinian side to the meetings of the Security 
Committee is chaired by 'Abd-al-Razzaq al-Yahya, deputy chairman 
of the delegation in the Gaza-Jericho Committee. The Israeli 
side is chaired by Uzi Dayan, deputy chairman of the Israeli 
delegation to the Gaza-Jericho Committee. 
  Dr. Nabil Sha'th, Palestinian President Yasir 'Arafat's 
political adviser and head of the Palestinian delegation to the 
Gaza-Jericho Committee, left Taba earlier today for Cairo to 
take part in President 'Arafat's talks with President Husni 
Mubarak. [passage omitted] Dr. Nabil Sha'th said that the 
upcoming meeting of the Gaza-Jericho Committee will meet in Taba 
on Monday to discuss the area of the settlements in Gaza. He 
expressed hope that an agreement would be reached with the 
Israeli side on this matter. 
  On another aspect, during its meeting today the Civilian 
Affairs Committee will finalize discussions on transferring the 
water and electricity authority to the Palestinian side. The 
committee yesterday completed agreement on transferring 25 
authorities from the Israeli side to the Palestinian side. 
There are still 13 authorities open for negotiations. 
  It is worth mentioning that the Civilian Affairs Committee 
is 
chaired on the Palestinian side by Lawyer Jamil al-Tarifi, and 
on the Israeli side by Gadi Zohar, in charge of civil 
administration in the West Bank. 

